# WHAT IT IS
#   `pavillion` is a **single-binary federated community-events
#   server** that runs as a long-lived daemon serving:
#
#     • An HTTP REST + ActivityPub Server-to-Server federation
#       surface for community events (one user account per local
#       community, each account holds the calendar of that
#       community's events; remote users on Mastodon, Lemmy,
#       Mobilizon, GoToSocial, Pleroma, Akkoma, Misskey, etc.
#       can follow a community's calendar as if it were a user
#       and receive event-creation activities into their AP
#       timeline)
#
#     • Native ICS-feed ingestion (the `import:sync` subcommand
#       pulls events from an external calendar URL — Google
#       Calendar / iCal / NextCloud / Sogo / Radicale — and
#       publishes them as native federated events)
#
#     • A Mobilizon-compatible event schema so events authored
#       on a Pavillion instance show up correctly when followed
#       from Mobilizon, and vice versa
#
#     • A backup + housekeeping subsystem with scheduled jobs
#       (daily DB backup + GFS retention, hourly disk-space
#       monitoring with configurable warning + critical
#       thresholds, post-backup GFS retention enforcement); the
#       `pavillion backup …` and `pavillion housekeeping` CLI
#       subcommands expose this subsystem for ops use inside a
#       Docker container (Pavillion is designed to run under
#       Docker, so the CLI is meant to be invoked via
#       `docker exec`).
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/server/cli/index.ts
#                       commander.js subcommand registrations;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetch of src/server/cli/index.ts)
#
#   pavillion <COMMAND> [SUBCOMMAND] [ARGS...] [OPTIONS...]
#
#   Top-level:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Print version (1.0.0)
#
#   Commands:
#     backup                         Backup management commands
#         create                     Queue an immediate backup
#                                    job (manual)
#         list                       List all available backups
#                                    (ID / Date / Size / Type /
#                                    Category / Verified)
#         status                     Show backup system health
#                                    and statistics (storage +
#                                    last successful backup +
#                                    GFS retention info)
#         restore <ID>               Restore database from a
#                                    backup by ID
#     housekeeping                   View housekeeping system
#                                    status (scheduled-job
#                                    inventory, disk-monitoring
#                                    config, warning + critical
#                                    thresholds)
#     import:sync [OPTIONS]          Manually sync an ICS import
#                                    source (or all verified
#                                    sources for a calendar)
#         --source-id <UUID>         Import source UUID to sync
#         --calendar-id <UUID>       Calendar UUID — sync all
#                                    verified sources for this
#                                    calendar
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `stephenhoward/pavillion` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `@fedify/fedify@^1.10.0` in its `package.json` (verified via
#   `gh api repos/stephenhoward/pavillion/contents/package.json`).
#
#   `@fedify/fedify` is **THE canonical TypeScript / JavaScript
#   ActivityPub server framework** — the cleanest, most mature,
#   most widely adopted TS-native ActivityPub server SDK on npm,
#   authored by **Hong Minhee** (洪 民憙) of the South Korean
#   open-source community.  The Fedify project ships as a multi-
#   package npm scope `@fedify/*`:
#
#     • `@fedify/fedify`             the core framework — the
#                                    typed `Federation<TContextData>`
#                                    builder with full dispatcher
#                                    registration for every
#                                    Actor lifecycle event
#                                    (inbox, outbox, followers,
#                                    following, featured, liked,
#                                    shared) plus typed callbacks
#                                    for every typed `as:Activity`
#                                    subclass — `Create`, `Update`,
#                                    `Delete`, `Follow`, `Accept`,
#                                    `Reject`, `Add`, `Remove`,
#                                    `Like`, `Dislike`, `Announce`,
#                                    `Undo`, `Block`, `Flag`,
#                                    `Listen`, `Read`, `View`,
#                                    `Move`, `Question`, `Travel`,
#                                    `Arrive`, `Leave`,
#                                    `TentativeAccept`,
#                                    `TentativeReject`, `Ignore`,
#                                    `Invite`, `Offer`,
#                                    plus the typed
#                                    `as:Object` subclass tree
#                                    (Note, Article, Image,
#                                    Audio, Video, Page,
#                                    Document, Event, Place,
#                                    Profile, Relationship,
#                                    Tombstone, Person, Group,
#                                    Application, Service,
#                                    Organization, Hashtag,
#                                    Mention, Emoji, ChatMessage)
#     • `@fedify/cli`                the `fedify` CLI toolchain
#                                    (lookup, webfinger, inbox,
#                                    nodeinfo, tunnel, init,
#                                    relay, generate-vocab)
#     • `@fedify/vocab`              the typed Activity Vocabulary
#                                    library (code-generated
#                                    from the AS2 + AP specs)
#     • `@fedify/vocab-runtime`      runtime helpers for the
#                                    code-generated vocab
#     • `@fedify/webfinger`          typed WebFinger client
#                                    library
#     • `@fedify/uri-template`       URI Template (RFC 6570)
#                                    utilities
#     • `@fedify/h3` / `@fedify/hono` / `@fedify/express` /
#       `@fedify/koa` / `@fedify/fastify` / `@fedify/nestjs` /
#       `@fedify/elysia` / `@fedify/next` / `@fedify/nuxt` /
#       `@fedify/astro` / `@fedify/solidstart` /
#       `@fedify/sveltekit` / `@fedify/cfworkers`
#                                    integration adapters for
#                                    every major Node.js + Bun
#                                    + Deno + Cloudflare Workers
#                                    web framework
#     • `@fedify/redis` /
#       `@fedify/postgres` /
#       `@fedify/sqlite` /
#       `@fedify/mysql` /
#       `@fedify/amqp`               KV store + queue driver
#                                    backends for delivery
#                                    queues, key stores, and
#                                    in-process state
#     • `@fedify/debugger`           embedded ActivityPub debug
#                                    dashboard
#     • `@fedify/relay`              ActivityPub relay support
